# Conventional Commits Template

Format: type(scope): imperative title under 50 chars

• Body content explaining the **what** and **why** (not how)
• Use Markdown syntax: **bold**, `code`, _italic_, bullet points
• Include affected components when relevant
• Reference issues/PRs at bottom

Types: feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|test|chore|perf|build|ci|revert
Add ! for breaking changes (e.g., feat!:)

Example:
feat(parser): add command parsing with error handling

• Implement parser state machine for **lexical analysis**
• Add support for `pipe`, `redirect_in/out/append/heredoc` tokens
• Include comprehensive error handling for syntax validation
• Parser handles command arguments and special token sequences

Fixes #123
